31/10/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The government reiterated it strong commitment to curbing human trafficking on Thursday (30 October) during the first meeting of a working group fighting child trafficking. 
The group consists of government representatives and the coalition Together Against Children Trafficking. 
Helga Conrad, who heads the human trafficking division at the Stability Pact, attended the meeting and said "child trafficking ? 
is not only an Albanian problem but a regional one." (ATA, BBC - 30/10/03)
